sentence: I was just sitting down to meet with some new therapy clients , a couple , and the building started shaking like crazy .
mut.sentence: I was just sitting down to meet with some new therapy clients , a couple of them , and the building they were in started shaking like crazy .
reason: 在原句中，'building'指的是发生摇晃的建筑物，即作者所在的建筑。而在变异句中，'building they were in'指的是作者提到的某些新疗法客户所在的建筑物，可能是指客户所在的另一个地方，不一定和作者在同一个建筑内。因此，两个句子中的目标词'building'含义有所不同。

sentence: They belong to a group of 15 ringers -- including two octogenarians and four youngsters in training -- who drive every Sunday from church to church in a sometimes-exhausting effort to keep the bells sounding in the many belfries of East Anglia .
mut.sentence: The group of 15 ringers, including the two octogenarians and the four youngsters in training, drive every Sunday from one church to another in a sometimes-exhausting effort to keep the bells sounding in the numerous belfries of East Anglia.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'drive'的含义相同，都是指开车或驾驶的意思。两个句子都描述了一组钟声敲击者每周日从一个教堂开车到另一个教堂，以保持East Anglia地区多个钟楼钟声的响起。两个句子中的'drive'都表达了同样的动作和目的，没有体现出含义上的差异。

sentence: The dinner was held at a Washington hotel hours after the court 's conference over the case .
mut.sentence: The dinner was held at the hotel in Washington hours after the court's conference over the case.
reason: 两个句子中的目标词‘hours’含义相同，都指的是在法庭会议结束后的几小时。‘hours’在这两个句子中都是表示时间的单位，没有因为句子结构的变化而产生不同的意义。

sentence: Then a wild thought ran circles through his clouded brain .
mut.sentence: Then a wild thought ran circles through the brain clouded by confusion.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'thought'的含义没有发生变化。'thought'在这两个句子中都是指思维、想法的意思。原句中的'clouded brain'和变异句中的'the brain clouded by confusion'都描述了大脑的状态，即大脑被困惑或混乱所笼罩，但并没有改变'thought'这个词本身的含义。

sentence: The Foundation organised , together with the European Commission , the Spanish Ministry of Social Affairs and the Galician regional government , a European conference on social exclusion : a major challenge for public welfare services .
mut.sentence: The Foundation organised, together with the European Commission, the Spanish Ministry of Social Affairs, and the Galician regional government, a European conference on social exclusion: a major challenge for Galician public welfare services.
reason: 原句中的目标词'public'指的是一般性的、全欧洲范围的福利服务，而变异句中的目标词'Galician public welfare services'特指加里西亚地区的公共福利服务，含义更为具体和地域化。因此，两个句子中目标词的含义有所不同。

sentence: My back is still in knots and my hands are still shaking .
mut.sentence: My back is still in these knots and my hands are still doing this shaking.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词 'knots' 的含义没有改变。'Knots' 在原句和变异句中都指的是背部紧张或疼痛的感觉，通常是由于压力或紧张引起的。变异句中的 'these knots' 并没有改变 'knots' 的含义，它仍然指代同样的身体状态。同样，变异句中的 'this shaking' 也没有改变 'shaking' 的含义，它仍然描述手的颤抖。因此，两个句子中的目标词含义相同。

sentence: A test using new `` genetic probes `` showed that little Will Quinlan had not inherited a damaged retinoblastoma supressor gene and , therefore , faced no more risk than other children of developing the rare cancer .
mut.sentence: A test using new genetic probes showed that little Will Quinlan had not inherited a damaged retinoblastoma supressor gene and, therefore, faced no more risk than those other children of developing the rare cancer.
reason: 原句和变异句中的目标词'inherited'含义相同，都表示小Will Quinlan没有从父母那里遗传到受损的视网膜母细胞瘤抑制基因。两个句子中'inherited'的使用情境和上下文没有改变，因此目标词的具体含义没有差异。

sentence: A test using new `` genetic probes `` showed that little Will Quinlan had not inherited a damaged retinoblastoma supressor gene and , therefore , faced no more risk than other children of developing the rare cancer .
mut.sentence: A test using new genetic probes showed that little Will Quinlan had not inherited a damaged retinoblastoma supressor gene and, therefore, faced no more risk than those other children of developing the rare cancer.

sentence: Back in the chase car , we drove around some more , got stuck in a ditch , enlisted the aid of a local farmer to get out the trailer hitch and pull us out of the ditch .
mut.sentence: Back in the chase car, we drove around some more, got stuck in a ditch, enlisted the aid of a local farmer to get out the trailer hitch and pull the chase car out of the ditch.

sentence: They will also tell you that even if you hate heights , you can still balloon .
mut.sentence: They will also tell you that even if you hate heights, you can still ride in a balloon.
reason: 原句中的'balloon'作为动词使用，意味着进行热气球飞行；而变异句中的'ride in a balloon'中的'balloon'作为名词使用，指的是乘坐热气球这一活动或热气球本身。因此，这两个句子中的'balloon'词性不同，含义也有所区别。

sentence: Vicar Marshall admits to mixed feelings about this issue , since he is both a vicar and an active bell-ringer himself .
mut.sentence: Vicar Marshall admits to mixed feelings about the issue, since he is both a vicar and an active bell-ringer himself.

sentence: Some found it on the screen of a personal computer .
mut.sentence: Some found the item on the screen of a personal computer.

sentence: The finding riveted medicine .

sentence: They are not accepted everywhere , however .

sentence: Goldman Sachs , JP Morgan Chase and Morgan Stanley had already repaid their support in June .
mut.sentence: Goldman Sachs, JP Morgan Chase and Morgan Stanley had already repaid the support from them in June.
reason: 在这两个句子中，目标词'support'的含义没有发生变化。原句和变异句中的'support'都指的是金融机构所获得的经济援助或资金支持，并且两个句子都表明这些支持已经被偿还。变异句中增加的'from them'并不改变'support'这个词本身的含义，只是更明确地指出了支持来自于这三家金融机构。

sentence: Not one thing in the house is where it is supposed to be , but the structure is fine .

sentence: That 's why I -- why I do a free job now and then .

sentence: But his new-found buddy had matched him drink for drink until he lost count , and the man 's eyes were still clear .

sentence: How many government programs and policies exist because they line the pockets of political insiders ?

sentence: What Gov. Clinton is advocating , in effect , is extending the educational system down to the pre-kindergarten years .
mut.sentence: What Gov. Clinton is advocating, in effect, is the extension of the educational system down to the pre-kindergarten years.
